content.title: Google Docs - LAMBDA-75848: Sign-up without applying for a specific job
content.layoutDescription: Text document with multiple headings and bullet points
content.visibleText:
1. Modify the Product.Z_Type... field to also contain 'Singles' (right now it is either Hire or Prime)
b. Pipeline fields will be used to indicate Signup pipeline
2. We don't need any kw/Intent information, because there will be no actual job page for this pipeline (i.e. no hook, etc.) just fill out required fields with placeholders
3. Reuse unused Product.Z_DisplayUrl(...) fields (Logos/awareness engineering)
a. It or no link
b. Track the actual page we came from because it's 1-many?
c. Modify the flow when the application for such pipeline arrives to Review 2: Move it to Marketplace
4. Prepare job recommendations and send the email to the candidate
Frontend
Ref: https://www.figma.com/design/2345tXlYjXjNk9hXs/Cr Rely on Product.Z_Type... field to render the application differently
2. The pipeline links to 'Product.Z_DisplayUrl' field (which will have a role page URL)
3. Hide the 'eliminate' and 'details' block
4. Hide all such 'applications' in the terminal stage from the list
5. Modify the apply page
Questions
1. What are application terminal status do we select? - Marketplace
2. Do we control the entry URL just like we do for URLs? - https://reason.com/jp/1234/kk/rosera/ai/future/la Do we want to allow candidates to take all badges regardless of the default? - Rejection Threshold = 0
